KZN premier Sihle Zikalala spoke with eNCA's Sally Burdett. Courtesy of #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - If you're found to be flouting COVID-19 regulations in KZN, expect a harsh penalty. Premier Sihle Zikalala warned that no big parties will be allowed this festive season. He is also promising repercussions for organisers of the Ballito Matric Rage festival. "The command council has taken a decision there must be consequences, we cannot leave the situation unattended," Zikalala said. READ: COVID-19: SA records 8,166 new cases Contact tracing of students who attended the event is underway. Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize announced on Wednesday that South Africa has entered the second wave of COVID-19 infections. Up to the last week, the increase was mainly in the Eastern and Western Cape in specific districts. *Watch the full interview above.